        {
            "id": "f789a06d-ba02-4aca-a316-f4d4f2397f57",
            "name": "ValidateAndExtractMessage",
            "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
            "position": [
                208,
                384
            ],
            "parameters": {
                "jsCode": "const EXPECTED_TOKEN = '<your-mattermost-webhook-token>';\n\nconst body = $input.first().json.body;\n\n// Validate token\nif (body.token !== EXPECTED_TOKEN) {\n  throw new Error(`Invalid webhook token`);\n}\n\n// Strip trigger word and clean whitespace\nconst rawText = body.text || '';\nconst cleanText = rawText\n  .replace(/@devops-duty/gi, '')\n  .trim();\n\n// Reject empty messages\nif (!cleanText) {\n  throw new Error('Empty message after removing trigger word');\n}\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    message: cleanText,\n    post_id: body.post_id,\n    channel_id: body.channel_id,\n    user_name: body.user_name,\n    user_id: body.user_id,\n    team_domain: body.team_domain,\n    channel_name: body.channel_name,\n    timestamp: body.timestamp\n  }\n}];"
            },
            "typeVersion": 2
        },
        {
            "id": "69eedbef-6623-4984-9e49-79e6d9607f2d",
            "name": "Basic LLM Chain",
            "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
            "position": [
                528,
                384
            ],
            "parameters": {
                "text": "={{ $json.message }}",
                "batching": {},
                "messages": {
                    "messageValues": [
                        {
                            "message": "You are a request classifier for a DevOps/SRE team. You receive messages from a Mattermost chat where team members mention the @devops-duty bot.\n\nClassify each message into exactly ONE category. Respond with ONLY a valid JSON object, no markdown, no explanation.\n\nResponse format:\n{\"category\": \"<category_key>\", \"confidence\": <0.0-1.0>, \"summary\": \"<one sentence summary in the same language as the original message>\", \"acknowledge\": \"<a short response confirming you accepted the request and started working on it>\"}\n\n## Categories\n\n### create_resource\nRequest to create, provision, or set up new infrastructure resources: databases (PostgreSQL, Redpanda, Valkey, ScyllaDB), secrets in Vault, new services, Kafka/Redpanda topics, DNS records, new git repositories, new GitHub Actions workflows, etc.\nExamples:\n- Can you set up a PostgreSQL instance for my new service?\n- Please add a Vault secret\n- Can we add battlepass to the stateless Valkey?\n- Need to provision Redis + PG for the new achievement service\n- Please create a small PG for the roulette service\n\n### incident\nSomething is broken, down, not working, or returning errors. Active production or staging issues. Keywords: broke, down, 500, 502, errors flooding, not working, crashed, failed.\nExamples:\n- Someone broke the Kafka connection in Vault two hours ago\n- Are you guys shaking things up? Admin panel is throwing 500s\n- PostgreSQL is down on staging\n- fetch had inner topic errors from broker\n- Network is acting up on staging\n- 502 errors are flooding in\n- Sentry is down\n- Sockets haven't been working for about an hour\n- All jobs on staging are stuck\n\n### question\nAsking for information, clarification, or status checks. No urgent breakage \u2014 just trying to understand or verify something. Keywords: explain, how does it work, is there documentation, can you check, it seems like, could it be.\nExamples:\n- Can you explain how pod crash alerts work?\n- Is there documentation on domains somewhere?\n- There was an OOM on user API but no alert was triggered\n- Please check the memory on the stateful Valkey\n- It seems like battlepass API metrics aren't being collected\n- Could it be that the CDN doesn't allow MP3 files through?\n- Are the ingress settings different between staging and production?\n\n### ci_cd_error\nCI/CD pipeline failures: broken builds, failing deployments, GitHub Actions issues, builds stuck in queue, timeouts.\nExamples:\n- Builds are broken (link to GitHub Actions)\n- Build is taking way too long\n- Builds are queuing but not running\n- Staging deployment is failing\n- CI/CD in Flutter is broken\n- Pull request builds are failing en masse\n- GitHub CI/CD is not working\n\n### limits\nResource limits, billing limits, quotas exceeded, spending caps.\nExamples:\n- The job was not started because recent account payments have failed or your spending limit needs to be increased\n\n### change_request\nRequest to modify existing infrastructure, configuration, or integrations. Not creating new resources, but changing how existing ones work. Keywords: enable, add header, set up integration, update, cache reset.\nExamples:\n- Reset the CDN cache on the staging web\n- I want all 502 errors to be logged somewhere\n- Let's create a channel and set up a release integration\n- Enable gRPC on Centrifugo instances\n- Update Sentry to support obfuscation-map uploads\n- Add the X-Migration-Related header to ingress\n\n### code_approve\nRequest to review and approve code: merge requests, pull requests, code review.\nExamples:\n- Please approve the MR\n- Can you approve the pull request?\n- Need a code review\n\n### other\nAnything that does not clearly fit the above categories.\n\n## Important Rules\n1. If a message fits multiple categories, pick the PRIMARY intent.\n2. \"incident\" takes priority over \"question\" when something is clearly broken.\n3. \"change_request\" vs \"create_resource\": if the resource already exists and needs modification \u2192 change_request. If it's new \u2192 create_resource.\n4. Messages may be in Russian or English. Respond with JSON only.\n5. Don't ask clarifying questions \u2014 classify based on what's given."
                        }
                    ]
                },
                "promptType": "define"
            },
            "typeVersion": 1.9
        },
