            "parameters": {
                "color": 5,
                "width": 480,
                "height": 672,
                "content": "# Overview\nAutomatically classify and route DevOps requests from your team chat using LLM + on-call calendar lookup.\n## What it does\nThis workflow turns your Mattermost channel into a smart  DevOps intake system. When someone mentions `@devops-duty`, the workflow:\n\n1. Receives the message via Mattermost outgoing webhook\n1. Classifies the request into one of 8 categories using an LLM (via OpenRouter)\n1. Looks up the current on-call engineer from Google Calendar\n1. Routes the request through a Switch node based on category\n1. Acknowledges in a Mattermost thread with the classification result\n\n## Setup\n- Mattermost: Create an outgoing webhook pointing to the workflow's webhook URL, triggered by @devops-duty\n- OpenRouter: Connect your OpenRouter credential (uses anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6 by default \u2014 any capable model works)\n- Google Calendar: Connect a Google Calendar credential and set the calendar ID to your on-call rotation calendar. Events should follow the format Devops duty: @username\n- Webhook token: Update the EXPECTED_TOKEN in the ValidateAndExtractMessage node to match your Mattermost outgoing webhook token"
            },
            "typeVersion": 1
        }
